  "description": "The default color palette of Tailwind CSS v4 — the most-used palette in the industry, hand-rebuilt in OKLCH for v4 (22 hues x 11 steps published as oklch CSS variables). The de facto baseline any generated scale must at least match.",
  "philosophy": "A classic 50-950 lightness ramp per hue, hand-tuned rather than formula-generated, republished in OKLCH for v4 so chroma and hue drift smoothly across steps (hue rotates within a scale, e.g. amber walks from ~95 to ~46 degrees as it darkens). Steps carry no documented semantics — designers pick steps by eye, with conventions emerging from the docs' own examples (500 solids, hover one step darker). There is no dark-mode palette: the same single scale is used in both modes via the dark: variant, typically by inverting which end you read from.",
