  "notes": "Single palette: Tailwind ships no dark-mode variants, so dark is null on every step — the dark: variant just re-reads the same scale (docs example: bg-white dark:bg-gray-800). Tailwind documents NO step semantics; the roleMapping above is limited to what its own docs examples ground: solid buttons at 500 (bg-sky-500, bg-violet-500, bg-indigo-500), hover one step darker (hover:bg-violet-600, active:bg-violet-700), timestamps/muted text at text-gray-500, and primary text at gray-950 (the docs' notification-card example and tailwindcss.com itself). Background/border roles are null because the docs prescribe nothing (app surfaces use plain white, outside the scale). Buttons pair 500 fills with text-white. Five interchangeable neutral families exist (slate, gray, zinc, neutral, stone); gray is extracted here. Values are the v4 hand-rebuilt OKLCH palette from theme.css, verbatim; --color-white: #fff and --color-black: #000 also exist outside the scales. No alpha or P3 variants are published — opacity is applied via utility modifiers (bg-blue-500/50) at use time."
